HEADWORD: Anthozoa
<hw>An`tho*zo"a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>'a`nqos</grk> flower + <?/ animal.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The class of the C⟦oe⟧lenterata which includes
the corals and sea anemones. The three principal groups or orders are
<spn>Acyonaria</spn>, <spn>Actinaria</spn>, and
<spn>Madreporaria</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

